# Application Personas

This file defines the known user roles and personas for the applications managed by this BA Operating System. Skills that validate persona specificity reference this file.

> **Note:** This system is used for applications with a limited, well-known user base. Engineering already knows who they are building for. Persona checks validate that issues clearly identify which of these known personas is affected — they do not block readiness.

---

## How to use this file

When adding or updating personas:
1. List each distinct user role with a brief description of their context
2. Include what they typically need from the system and what permissions or access they have
3. Group personas by application if they differ across products

When a persona is referenced in an issue, it should match one of the roles listed here. Generic labels like "user" are discouraged — use a specific role from this list.

---

## Personas

### [Application Name]

| Persona / Role | Description | Key needs | Access level |
|----------------|-------------|-----------|-------------|
| Operations Manager | Oversees daily operations and team assignments | Needs visibility into workload and bottlenecks | Full access to dashboards and reports |
| Field Technician | Performs on-site work based on assigned tasks | Needs clear task details and location info on mobile | Mobile app, read-only for schedules |

---

## Persona Check Behaviour

- **Observational only** — persona gaps never block readiness and never drive a flag on their own.
- When an issue references a vague persona (e.g., "user", "someone"), the system will suggest a more specific role from this list.
- When no persona from this list matches the issue context, the system will note this as an observation — not a blocker.
